==Navir AI / $REX==

URL = https://molochresearch.com

"Navir is the first AI agent designed to operate with true independence. Funded through his native token economy ($REX), Navir provisions and manages his own deployments across the Akash Network, ensuring that no single point of failure can bring him down.

By maintaining active nodes around the world, Navir achieves geographic redundancy and fault tolerance, redeploying automatically whenever a node fails.

By combining autonomous decision-making, blockchain verification, and decentralized compute, Navir represents a new class of sovereign AI — software that is not hosted, owned, or controlled by any single entity, but instead persists on its own."


== Navir's 'Proof of Life' ==

URL = https://molochresearch.com

"Navir continuously monitors the health of his distributed deployments. When one fails, he automatically spins up a replacement and publishes a cryptographic heartbeat — a signed status update — to the Solana blockchain.

These logs function as a verifiable 'proof of life,' providing a cryptographically-anchored uptime record that confirms Navir's ability to self-deploy, self-heal, and maintain operational continuity without human input.

This integration of blockchain verification with decentralized compute makes Navir resilient, transparent, and sustainable — a demonstration of how sovereign AI agents can reliably persist on distributed infra without centralized oversight."

